sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: Frozen post-mortem pituitaries were broken into small pieces in a frozen mortar on dry-ice, and one piece was thawed on ice and prepared for nuclei extraction based on a modified protocol from (Mathys, Davila-Velderrain et al. 2019).  The remainder of one pituitary was pulverized.  Part of the powder was collected to be also processed following the same protocol. The remaining powder and pituitary fragments were stored back at -80C.
sample_growth_protocol_ch1: Frozen post-mortem human pituitaries were obtained from the National Institutes of Health (NIH) NeuroBioBank, and kept at -80C until processing.
sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Briefly, and all on ice, RNAse inhibitor (NEB MO314L) was added to the homogenization buffer (0.32 M sucrose, 1 mM EDTA, 10 mM Tris-HCl, pH 7.4, 5mM CaCl2, 3mM Mg(Ac)2, 0.1% IGEPAL CA-630), 50% OptiPrep (Stock is 60% Media from Sigma; cat# D1556), 35% OptiPrep and 30% OptiPrep right before isolation. Each pituitary was homogenized in a dounce glass homogenizer (1ml, VWR cat# 71000-514), and the homogenate filtered through a 40 mm cell strainer. An equal volume of 50% OptiPrep was added, and the  ...
sample_data_processing: Single Nuclei ATAC-seq data of frozen post-mortem human pituitary samples were processed using Cell Ranger-ATAC pipeline version 1.2.0., Samples were aligned to the CellRanger-ATAC GRCh38 reference genome.
supplementary_files_format_and_content: Peak accessibility count matrices for cell barcodes in Hierarchical Data Format HDF5.Metadata files that include per barcode QC, ATAC signal and cell calling metrics in comma-separated values (CSV) format.BED-like tabular files listing all unique fragments captured by the assay in tab-separated values (TSV) format.

sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: The frozen post-mortem pituitary was pulverized in a frozen mortar on dry-ice and part of the obtained powder was thawed on ice and prepared for nuclei extraction based on a modified protocol from (Mathys, Davila-Velderrain et al. 2019). The remainder of the pituitary was stored back at -80C.
sample_growth_protocol_ch1: The frozen post-mortem human pituitary used for multiome was obtained from the National Institutes of Health (NIH) NeuroBioBank, and kept at -80C until processing.
sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Briefly, and all on ice, RNAse inhibitor (NEB MO314L) was added to the homogenization buffer (0.32 M sucrose, 1 mM EDTA, 10 mM Tris-HCl, pH 7.4, 5mM CaCl2, 3mM Mg(Ac)2, 0.1% IGEPAL CA-630), 50% OptiPrep (Stock is 60% Media from Sigma; cat# D1556), 35% OptiPrep and 30% OptiPrep right before isolation. Each pituitary was homogenized in a dounce glass homogenizer (1ml, VWR cat# 71000-514), and the homogenate filtered through a 40 mm cell strainer. An equal volume of 50% OptiPrep was added, and the  ...
sample_data_processing: Single nuclei Multiome (ATAC + Gene Expression) data were processed using the Cell Ranger ARC pipeline version 1.0.0., Indices from two GEM wells were pooled together and processed as a single sample., Samples were aligned to the CellRanger-ARC GRCh38 reference transcriptome.  Intron-aligned reads were included in the gene expression counts.
supplementary_files_format_and_content: Count matrices for cell barcodes in Hierarchical Data Format HDF5.  File includes both Gene Expression UMI counts and ATAC peak fragment counts.BED-like tabular file listing all unique fragments captured by the ATAC assay in tab-separated values (TSV) format.
